paragraphs.title: Instructions
paragraphs.text:
%md
1. Run `Download games` (will take ~60s)
2. Run `Start streaming` in parallel
3. Run SQL

msg.data:
1. Run Download games (will take ~60s)
  2. Run Start streaming in parallel
  3. Run SQL

paragraphs.title: Download games
paragraphs.text:
%sh echo "Downloading dependencies" apt-get install -y jq STEAM_DIR="/data/steam" STEAM_GAMES_DIR="$STEAM_DIR/games" TOP_GAMES="$STEAM_DIR/top.csv" GAMES="$STEAM_DIR/games.csv" mkdir -p "$STEAM_DIR" "$STEAM_GAMES_DIR" echo -e "id,name\n$(curl -s "https://store.steampowered.com/stats" | grep "gameLink" | sed 's/.*href=".*app\///; s/<.*>//; s/\/.*>/,/; s/[^0-9]*>/,/' | tr -d '\r')" > "$TOP_GAMES" APP_COLUMNS="steam_appid type name required_age is_free header_image developers[] publishers[] price_overview.currency price_overview.initial price_overview.final price_overview.discount_percent platforms.windows platforms.mac platforms.linux pc_requirements.minimum pc_requirements.recommended mac_requirements.minimum mac_requirements.recommended linux_requirements.minimum linux_requirements.recommended metacritic.score metacritic.url recommendations.total release_date.coming_soon release_date.date" REVIEWS_COLUMNS="query_summary.num_reviews query_summary.review_score query_summary.review_score_desc query_summary.total_positive query_summary.total_negative query_summary.total_reviews" #rm "$STEAM_GAMES_DIR"/* REFRESH=false while read line; do ID=$(echo "$line" | sed 's/,.*//') NAME=$(echo "$line" | sed 's/.*,//') FILE="$STEAM_GAMES_DIR/$ID" TMP_FILE="/tmp/games-tmp-$ID-$RANDOM.csv" if [ "$ID" == "id" ]; then continue; fi if [ -f "$FILE" ]; then TIMESTAMP=$(date +%s) GAME_TIMESTAMP=$(tail -1 "$FILE" | sed 's/.*,//g') DIFFERENCE=$(($TIMESTAMP-$GAME_TIMESTAMP)) if [ $REFRESH != true ]; then echo "Cached $ID $NAME (refresh disabled)" continue fi if [ $DIFFERENCE -le 300 ]; then echo "Cached $ID $NAME (cached file is $DIFFERENCE seconds old)" continue else echo "Refreshing $ID $NAME (cached file is $DIFFERENCE seconds old)" rm "$FILE" fi else echo "Processing $ID $NAME" fi echo -n "... adding header " for COLUMNS in "$APP_COLUMNS" "$REVIEWS_COLUMNS"; do for COLUMN in $COLUMNS; do echo -n "$COLUMN," done done | sed 's/\./_/g; s/[[]]//g; s/date_date/date/g; s/release_date_coming_soon/coming_soon/g; s/query_summary_//g' > "$TMP_FILE" echo "current_players,timestamp" >> "$TMP_FILE" echo "[DONE]" echo -n "... downloading details " JSON=$(curl -s "https://store.steampowered.com/api/appdetails/?appids=$ID") SUCCESS=$(echo "$JSON" | jq ".\"$ID\".success" | awk '{print $1}') if [ $SUCCESS != true ]; then echo "[FAILED]" continue; fi echo "[DONE]" for COLUMN in $APP_COLUMNS; do VALUE=$(echo "$JSON" | jq -r ".\"$ID\".data.$COLUMN" 2>/dev/null || echo "") VALUE=$(echo "$VALUE" | sed -e 's/"//g; s/
  • /\ /g; s//\ /g; s/<[^>]*>//g; s/\ /
    /g; s/\s\s*/ /g' | head -1) if [[ $VALUE =~ ^[0-9]+$ ]] || [ "$VALUE" == true ] || [ "$VALUE" == false ] || [ "$VALUE" == TRUE ] || [ "$VALUE" == FALSE ]; then echo -n "$VALUE," else if [ "$VALUE" != "" ] && [ "$VALUE" != "null" ]; then echo -n "\"$VALUE\"" fi echo -n , fi done >> "$TMP_FILE" echo -n "... downloading reviews " JSON=$(curl -s "https://store.steampowered.com/appreviews/$ID?json=1") SUCCESS=$(echo "$JSON" | jq ".success" | awk '{print $1}') if [ $SUCCESS -ne 1 ]; then echo "[FAILED]" continue; fi echo "[DONE]" for COLUMN in $REVIEWS_COLUMNS; do VALUE=$(echo "$JSON" | jq -r ".$COLUMN" 2>/dev/null || echo "") VALUE=$(echo "$VALUE" | sed -e 's/"//g; s/\s\s*/ /g' | head -1) if [[ $VALUE =~ ^[0-9]+$ ]] || [ "$VALUE" == true ] || [ "$VALUE" == false ] || [ "$VALUE" == TRUE ] || [ "$VALUE" == FALSE ]; then echo -n "$VALUE," else if [ "$VALUE" != "" ] && [ "$VALUE" != "null" ]; then echo -n "\"$VALUE\"" fi echo -n , fi done >> "$TMP_FILE" echo -n "... downloading current stats " JSON=$(curl -s "https://api.steampowered.com/ISteamUserStats/GetNumberOfCurrentPlayers/v1/?appid=$ID") RESULT=$(echo "$JSON" | jq -r ".response.result" | awk '{print $1}') if [ $RESULT -eq 1 ]; then echo "[DONE]" echo -n "$(echo "$JSON" | jq -r ".response.player_count")," >> "$TMP_FILE" else echo "[UNKNOWN]" echo -n "0," >> "$TMP_FILE" fi date +%s >> "$TMP_FILE" echo "DONE (stored as $FILE)" mv "$TMP_FILE" $FILE done < "$TOP_GAMES" for FILE in $(find "$STEAM_GAMES_DIR" -type f); do tail -1 $FILE done >> "$GAMES" echo "Files: $(find "$STEAM_GAMES_DIR" -type f | wc -l)"

paragraphs.title: Start streaming
paragraphs.text:
%spark
import org.apache.spark.streaming._
import org.apache.spark.sql.streaming._
import org.apache.spark.sql.types._
import spark.implicits._

// retrieve schema from files
// val schema = spark.read.
//     format("com.databricks.spark.csv").  // use CSV format
//     option("header", "true").            // first line is header
//     option("inferSchema", "true").       // infer data typesload("/data/steam/games")
//     load("/data/steam/games").           // path to directory
//     schema

// schema definition
val schema = StructType(
    Seq(StructField("steam_appid",IntegerType,true),
      StructField("type",StringType,true), StructField("name",StringType,true),
      StructField("required_age",IntegerType,true), StructField("is_free",BooleanType,true),
      StructField("header_image",StringType,true), StructField("developers",StringType,true),
      StructField("publishers",StringType,true), StructField("price_overview_currency",StringType,true),
      StructField("price_overview_initial",IntegerType,true), StructField("price_overview_final",IntegerType,true),
      StructField("price_overview_discount_percent",IntegerType,true), StructField("platforms_windows",BooleanType,true),
      StructField("platforms_mac",BooleanType,true), StructField("platforms_linux",BooleanType,true),
      StructField("pc_requirements_minimum",StringType,true), StructField("pc_requirements_recommended",StringType,true),
      StructField("mac_requirements_minimum",StringType,true), StructField("mac_requirements_recommended",StringType,true),
      StructField("linux_requirements_minimum",StringType,true), StructField("linux_requirements_recommended",StringType,true),
      StructField("metacritic_score",IntegerType,true), StructField("metacritic_url",StringType,true),
      StructField("recommendations_total",IntegerType,true), StructField("coming_soon",BooleanType,true),
      StructField("release_date",StringType,true), StructField("num_reviews",IntegerType,true),
      StructField("review_score",IntegerType,true), StructField("review_score_desc",StringType,true),
      StructField("total_positive",IntegerType,true), StructField("total_negative",IntegerType,true),
      StructField("total_reviews",LongType,true), StructField("current_players",LongType,true),
      StructField("timestamp",IntegerType,true)))

// read files written in a directory as a stream of data
val gamesStream = spark.readStream.
    format("com.databricks.spark.csv").     // use CSV format
    schema(schema).                         // use our schema
    option("header", "true").               // first line is header
    option("path", "/data/steam/games").    // path to directory
    load()

// create view games
val query = gamesStream.writeStream.
    format("memory").                   // output is stored in memory as an in-memory table
    queryName("steam").                 // table name
    outputMode(OutputMode.Append()).    // use entire updated table (storage connector to decides how to handle writing of the entire table)
    start()

%sql
SELECT count(steam_appid) AS proccessed FROM steam

paragraphs.title: Best games from 2018 & 2017
paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT release_date, SUBSTRING(name, 0, 16), metacritic_score FROM steam WHERE (release_date LIKE "%2018" OR release_date LIKE "%2017") AND metacritic_score > 60

paragraphs.title: Linux Vs. Windows Vs. MAC
paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT (SELECT count(steam_appid) FROM steam WHERE platforms_mac = true) AS macOS, (SELECT count(steam_appid) FROM steam WHERE platforms_linux = true) AS linux, (SELECT count(steam_appid) FROM steam WHERE platforms_windows = true) AS windows

paragraphs.title: Overall review score
paragraphs.text:
%sql 
SELECT name, review_score, review_score_desc FROM steam ORDER BY review_score

paragraphs.title: Top 5 currently played games
paragraphs.text:
%sql

SELECT name, current_players FROM steam ORDER BY current_players DESC LIMIT 5

paragraphs.title: Top 5 metacritic games
paragraphs.text: %sql SELECT SUBSTRING(name, 0, 16) as name, metacritic_score AS metacritic, (review_score*10) AS users  FROM steam ORDER BY metacritic_score  DESC LIMIT 5

paragraphs.title: Top 5 user games
paragraphs.text: %sql SELECT SUBSTRING(name, 0, 16) as name, metacritic_score  AS metacritic,(review_score*10) AS users FROM steam WHERE metacritic_score IS NOT NULL ORDER BY users  DESC LIMIT 5
